The article summarizes remarks made by President Trump during the National Day of Prayer event held on May 7, 2020. The President expressed gratitude to First Lady Melania Trump for her work on the BE BEST Initiative and for her efforts in fighting the drug addiction problem in the country. He called upon Americans to join their voices and hearts in prayer, asking for strength, solace, courage, comfort, hope, healing, recovery, and renewal. The President also thanked Vice President Mike Pence and his wife, Karen, for their work on the task force and praised the efforts of frontline workers, scientists, researchers, and faith leaders in helping the nation during the COVID-19 pandemic. Several faith leaders from different religions offered prayers and blessings, and a choir performed the songs "God Bless America" and "I Lift My Eyes Up."